snippet: “Outside People,” a smart but slight comedy of manners by Zayd Dohrn, follows a young American trying to make his way in business and the bedroom in the booming new China.
abstract: Charles Isherwood reviews Zayd Dohrn play Outside People, directed by Evan Cabnet at the Vineyard Theater; Matt Dellapina and Nelson Lee star.
lead_paragraph: “Outside People,” a smart but slight comedy of manners by Zayd Dohrn, follows a young American trying to make his way in business and the bedroom in the booming new China.
